commit.message:
Add assertions

* Assert that we leaked zero bytes in test_leaks_client.
* Rename test_leaks_server to test_leaks_server_linux, and skip this test if we're not on Linux, because the method used to check for leaked file descriptors is specific to Linux.
* Assert that test_leaks_server_linux doesn't leak any FDs
* This change includes no "guaranty's", only "guarantees"

commit.message:
Merge pull request #60 from behackett/oldpybuildfixes

Fix building on older Pythons
Fix one more build issue

Use destructors to free client and server state

This change obsoletes the functions authGSSClientClean and
authGSSServerClean. The client and server state are now
destroyed when the PyCapsule / PyCObject storing them are
reclaimed. The functions remain to avoid breaking backward
compatibility, but just return AUTH_GSS_COMPLETE.

Resolves #48.
